pressure,
politics, belief, and facts.

47:36.353 --> 47:42.359 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Miles O'Brien, the "PBS
NewsHour," New York.

47:42.393 --> 47:55.740 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: This week,
"Independent Lens"
on PBS is presenting a
captivating reexamination

47:55.773 --> 47:59.176 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of America's first mass school
shooting.

47:59.210 --> 48:05.449 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
"Tower" includes archival
footage, new animation
and untold witness stories who
unpack the

48:05.483 --> 48:12.790 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
horror that left 16 dead and
three dozen wounded
at the University of Texas,
Austin, in 1966.

48:12.823 --> 48:19.497 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, Texas is one of nine
states that allow
concealed weapons to be carried
on public

48:19.530 --> 48:25.603 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
college campuses, prompting
vigorous debate,
as we see in this "Independent
Lens" extra.

48:25.636 --> 48:34.411 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NICK ROLAND, Student: My name is
Nick Roland.
I'm a Ph.D student here at U.T.
Should be

48:34.445 --> 48:39.617 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
graduating this year with a
degree in U.S.
history. Went to Virginia Tech
for undergrad.

48:39.650 --> 48:42.620 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I was active-duty Army for
four years.

48:42.653 --> 48:46.824 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
My routine is just like anyone
else. You know,
I get up, eat breakfast. The
only difference

48:46.857 --> 48:51.695 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is that I put a handgun in my
bag before I
get on my bike and ride to
campus.

48:51.729 --> 49:00.004 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, this is it. I know that it's
loaded. It's
got the loaded chamber
indicator. So, then

49:00.037 --> 49:07.044 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I'm just going to place it here.

49:07.077 --> 49:11.816 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Once I get to campus, typically
going to go
somewhere where I can discreetly
put my weapon

49:11.849 --> 49:20.157 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on my hip. And I'm just going to
holster it
and then place it right here on
my hip.

49:20.191 --> 49:25.095 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHAEL CARGILL, Owner, Central
Texas Gun
Works: Campus carry went into
effect August

49:25.129 --> 49:30.835 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the 1st of 2016, which means
that a person
with a handgun license can now
carry a handgun,

49:30.868 --> 49:34.738 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
concealed, inside of a building
of a college
campus.

49:34.772 --> 49:37.508 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
My name is Michael Cargill. I'm
the owner
of Central Texas Gun Works,
which is a gun

49:37.541 --> 49:42.046 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
store here in Austin, Texas. I
carry a .45,
a .38 Special, and a
.9-millimeter. I love

49:42.079 --> 49:46.450 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it. I like walking to the
grocery store. I
like going to the movie
theaters. I like going

49:46.483 --> 49:48.118 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to all those places.

49:48.152 --> 49:52.189 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And now finally we can carry
those same facilities
on a college campus. Woo-hoo!

49:52.223 --> 49:53.190 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(APPLAUSE)

49:53.224 --> 49:54.592 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

49:54.625 --> 49:58.629 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANA LOPEZ, Student: Hey, how do
you all feel
about guns on campus?

49:58.662 --> 49:59.797 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
WOMAN: Weird.

49:59.830 --> 50:02.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANA LOPEZ: Come support Students
Against Campus
Carry.

50:02.366 --> 50:07.404 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
My name is Ana Lopez. I'm a
sophomore at the
University of Texas. And I'm
vice president

50:07.438 --> 50:09.573 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of Students Against Campus Carry
at U.T.

50:09.607 --> 50:11.976 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Invite your friends to stop by
and sign up.

50:12.009 --> 50:17.414 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A college campus is somewhere
where you should
be able to argue with someone
and have different

50:17.448 --> 50:23.053 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
beliefs. And in the presence of
guns, my freedom
of speech personally is totally
stifled.

50:23.087 --> 50:26.557 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN: The final version is due
Tuesday in class?

50:26.590 --> 50:28.626 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA MOORE, Professor,
University of Texas,
Austin: I'm Lisa Moore and I'm a
professor

50:28.659 --> 50:32.897 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of English and women's and
gender studies
here at the University of Texas,
Austin.

50:32.930 --> 50:38.435 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The campus carry law makes it
really hard
for us to do our jobs as
instructors. Students

50:38.469 --> 50:44.975 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are allowed to bring guns to my
classroom.
I really consider that
interchange of teaching

50:45.009 --> 50:49.380 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and learning that happens in a
college classroom
to be something of a sacred
vocation.

50:49.413 --> 50:56.587 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It has introduced a level of
tension, a level
of wariness into the classroom
setting that

50:56.620 --> 51:00.457 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I just find kind of
heartbreaking, frankly.

51:00.491 --> 51:03.027 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
MAN: Fire.

51:03.060 --> 51:04.929 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(GUNSHOTS)

51:04.962 --> 51:11.568 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: And this is about their
personal safety.
They are civilians that are
carrying the firearm

51:11.602 --> 51:13.404 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for personal protection.

51:13.437 --> 51:17.775 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JIM LEHRER, PBS: More than 30
people were
shot to death today at Virginia
Tech University

51:17.808 --> 51:22.613 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in Blacksburg, Virginia. It was
the deadliest
mass shooting in American
history.

51:22.646 --> 51:27.918 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NICK ROLAND: I was a senior that
year when
it happened. It was hard because
I really

51:27.952 --> 51:34.325 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
loved Virginia Tech. And I think
it's a really
special campus and community.
So, yes, it

51:34.358 --> 51:39.563 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was shocking, traumatic. It felt
like somebody
had attacked my family.

51:39.596 --> 51:43.534 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Had someone in one of those
classrooms been
armed, I think it would have
made a difference,

51:43.567 --> 51:49.073 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
certainly. People do deserve to
have a fighting
chance. And the concealed carry
gives them

51:49.106 --> 51:52.142 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
